{
  "texts": [
    "However, our roots are in the tradition of devising formal logics that can capture human-level cognition, not mathematical reasoning or anything of the sort (see Bringsjord et al., 2023c).",
    "In a word, mathematical logic has for over two millennia been purely extensional. 2.",
    "We straddle formal deductive logic and formal inductive logic; the latter is not on Davis's radar screen.",
    "The phrase \"inductive logic\" (nor any equivalent) does not occur in Davis (2017).",
    "Given that the work surveyed therein is avowedly aligned with mathematical logic (as we have pointed out), this is unsurprising."
  ]
}